subSubSection.paragraph:
A tidal pool (
33°13.949'N
; 
126°30.653'E
) on Beophwan beach, Seoguipo-shi, Jeju Island, Korea.

Prosome (Fig. 1
A-B
) 4-segmented, comprising cephalosome and 3 free pedigerous somites. P1-bearing somite fused to cephalosome. Cephalosome (Fig. 1A) with few sensilla and smooth posterior margin. Other prosomites with few sensilla on dorsal and lateral surfaces. Dorsal tegumental windows of elongated oval shape, one on cephalosome and one on three succeeding prosomites; 2 windows on genital double somite (Fig. 1A). Pleural areas well developed and rounded, without lobate posterolateral angles.

Rostrum (Fig. 1
A-C
) well developed, trapezoid with smooth anterior apex, clearly defined at base. Dorsal surface smooth with pair of sensilla at apical margin.
